        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p><placeName>La Fayette</placeName> Inc <date>24 June 5617</date></p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Revd &amp; Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">My engagements are brief,<lb/> &amp; so are yours; allow me
                therefore<lb/> to ask of you an immediate reply<lb/> upon the following
                questions.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">1. Whether the <add>שוחט</add> is not allowed to<lb/> Kill for a
                member of his Congren on<lb/>
                <add>יו"ט</add> when called upon; after he hath<lb/> prepared his <add>חלוק</add>
                &amp;c <add>כדינא</add> on <add>ערב יוט</add>?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">2. Whether the <add>שוחט</add> is bound to ask<lb/> the party that
                desire his services, say,<lb/> to kill an <add>עוף</add>, whether it is for<lb/> a
                sick person? (consequently, if it<lb/> is not for a sick person he must<lb/> not
                kill it!)</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">3. rdly <del>Whether the <add>שוחט</add> has</del> Upon which day of
                    <add>יוט</add> the <add>שוחט</add><lb/> has more permission, according</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>to <add>אורח חיים</add> &amp;c &amp;c<lb/> on the first or on the second?<lb/> I
                shall esteem it a particular favor, if you have<lb/> the goodness in answering<lb/>
                me the above <sic>querries</sic><lb/> as soon as possible.</p>
            <p>It's most astonishing<lb/> how pious people (that<lb/> violate the
                    <date>Sabbath</date> &amp;c<lb/> &amp; defile the Law of <add>אכילת
                כשר</add><lb/> &amp;c. &amp; never enter the gate<lb/> of a Syn.) are, that
                when<lb/> they see that the <add>שוחט</add><lb/> hath Nulled a chicken<lb/> on the
                first day <add>יוט</add> for</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>a member; they<lb/>
                <sic>challeng</sic> &amp; abuse<lb/> the <add>שוחט</add> for being<lb/> very
                indifferent<lb/> to his duty! And<lb/> of cause, who shall<lb/> decide upon
                such<lb/> matters? if I offer<lb/> them the <add>בספר דינים</add> they<lb/> can't
                read—nor have<lb/> they faith in the translation<lb/> of a person so wicked<lb/>
                (according to their <sic>oppinion</sic>) as<lb/> to kill an <add>יוט</add> when
                    <del>aft</del> demanded<lb/> of him! Yr kind answer<lb/> I will show to justify
                my=<lb/>self. Yrs faithfully</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">H Lowenthal</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p>N. B.</p>
            <p>Shall the <add>שוחט</add> be<lb/> guided in his capacity<lb/> by <hi rend="underline"
                    >some</hi> of his con.<lb/> (which seek their<lb/> destruction &amp; not<lb/>
                their welfare) or by<lb/> the <add>דינים</add> appertaining<lb/> to <add>ענין
                    שחיטות</add> where<lb/> shall <hi rend="underline">he</hi> or <hi
                    rend="underline">they</hi> seek<lb/> redress &amp; upon whose<lb/> judgment
                &amp;c ought they<lb/> to rely? A comment on the<lb/> above theme in yr next
                    <sic>valle.</sic><lb/> magazine will be gratefully<lb/> admired. <persName
                    role="author">H. L.</persName></p>
        </body>
